headline: Digital Asset Allocations Continue to Grow in Client Portfolios, DACFP Survey Finds
summary: Nineteen percent (19%) of financial advisors say that more than half of their clients have made allocations to digital assets in their portfolios, according to the Q3 2024 Advisor Pulse Survey, sponsored by Franklin Templeton Digital Assets and conducted by the Digital Assets Council of Financial Professionals (DACFP).
